TY  - JOUR
TI  - Qualitative Economics and Morishima Matrices
AU  - Bassett, Lowell
AU  - Habibagahi, Hamid
AU  - Quirk, James
AB  - [This paper investigates the interrelationships among Samuelson's correspondence principle, quasi-dominant diagonal matrices, and Morishima matrices, in the context of a qualitatively specified environment. In addition, the stability properties of the Morishima case are studied under the competitive assumptions that Walras' Law holds and excess demand functions are homogeneous of degree zero in prices.]
C1  - Full publication date: Apr., 1967
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1909110
